entries.femaleVariant: [Get out]
Let's go.
We have company.
Get yourself primed.
Dammit! Hansen's goons!
Hey. In the car, now.
[Get in]
They followed you.
Mighta started with a metro camfeed.
Dunno how they found us.
Here's hoping we're not too late.
No idea how they tracked me.
Hardly matters now.
[Get in]
So what – supposed to drag her around with me?
She doe'n't need a sitter.
Was I s'posed to drag her along while cruisin' around?
Myers can take care of herself. Not a damsel in distress. Saw her… take charge.
Safe? A derelict building in Dogtown? Just listen to how that sounds.
You left her alone… in Dogtown?
She is the President.
No tail – so that was a fuckin' lie?
Abandoned building on Elizabeth Kress.
Not gonna like this…
Just FYI... Not so sure you're gonna like it.
entries.maleVariant: Just, uh, FYI... Not so sure you're gonna like it.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah. Me too. It's not her first rodeo.
Hm. Actually…
Look, place seemed plenty safe to me.
Survived a few assassination attempts. Real tough… but still…
Hold up, I need to take this.
Boss man. I work the door at a club – selection, y'know - bouncin'…
That your cover?
An FIA agent working as a bouncer…?
Huh. That your lie-low gig – a bouncer?
FIA special agent… bouncin' away time at a club?
It pays the bills and nets me a little disposable.
Sleeper agents aren't entitled to government pay. Not even under the table.
The job attracts ex-cops and commandos, too. I know a few…
Heh, this is not how I imagined spending my day off.
Savin' the President... Great action-BD shit right there, amirite?
Yeah, sure, I guess so.
Does Myers still smoke?
Yeah, why?
Ain't no snitch.
Had a ciggie on a balcony this mornin'. Why you ask?
Snitches get stitches, man.
Hmmph… When things start to spiral outta control, she's likely to light up.
It's high time we help her out.
Why you callin' me on my day off?
Last I heard, you're the manager… Ask Bob, he owes me a favor anyway.
Yeah well, tough nuts. You'll have to manage without me.
They're a tough bunch. Troubled. Easy to blend in with over beers.
So that would be a yes. Not good…
Won't go anywhere without a destination.
Mighta tagged me off a metro camfeed. Did our damndest to stay off the streets.
Big step down from special agent.
Can think of one thing we have in common – both got potential we're wastin'.
Bein' on Arasaka's payroll is realizing one's potential?
Got a grudge? 'Saka step on your toes that hard?
Yeah. They tried to off me, botched it, end of story. You tell me.
That makes two things in common. Though somethin' tells me we won't stop at that.
entries.maleVariant: Makes two things in common. Though somethin' tells me we won't stop at that.

entries.femaleVariant: Uh-oh…
Argh, fuck! They beat us here!
Fucking preem…
Follow close behind!
Uuugh…
You're awake. Good.
I scanned your profile. Paints an interesting picture.
You gonked outta your mind?! You know who sent me, know we're on the same side?!
entries.maleVariant: You gonked outta your mind?! Know who sent me, know we're on the same side?!

entries.femaleVariant: You fucked in the head?!
Got aspirin here. Should help.
Freelance merc. You were born in NC, Heywood. To make things more interesting… FIA agent, you received your commission last night.
That would be you introduced. As for me – my name is Reed.
Wasn't so hard, was  it?
Sleeper agent brought out of slumber?
Sleeper agent got a wake-up call? Hell-o, good morning.
Isn't that better? No need for mystery, no need to complicate things.
Nomad, Bakker clan, no longer extant. Now a freelance merc. To make things more interestin'… FIA agent, you received your commission last night.
Arasaka counterintelligence. Terminated for undisclosed reasons. Now – a freelance merc, working for the FIA as of last night.
Introductions aside, let's get down to business.
So… is she safe?
She was in the morning.
No, not if we waste any more time here.
Seemed safe enough this mornin'. Hopin' it's still the case.
Less so the longer we dawdle.
[Take aspirin] Thanks.
Ugh... Yeah, thanks.
[Take aspirin] Playin' nice now?
Ugh… time to play good cop?
I don't think there is either.
It's not poison. I promise.
Consider it a gesture of good will.
Before we go…
You're not in the biz, V, our biz.
One thing eludes me – what drove you to get entangled in this mess?
Songbird hired me.
Just a gig.
Songbird hired me. Know her?
So Mi…
Somethin' up?
We used to work together.
Honestly? It's just another gig.
Address, please.
I agree completely.
So do I. We'll know soon.
Not on the strange side?
Abandoned building on Kress Street. Eighth floor.
I thought I'd heard the last about her, but... the girl's a magnet for trouble.
Right. It's time we paid our friend in distress a visit.
Fine, it's fine.
Nice to meet ya too.
Actually, I am – since yesterday.
What gave it away?
You got into a stranger's car.
You're lucky I am who I claim to be…
Odd introduction, but nice meetin' ya too, Reed.
Actually, I am though... just since yesterday.
entries.maleVariant: Actually, I am... Though just since yesterday.

entries.femaleVariant: Oh, what gave me away?
I was about to say your first times out are the hardest, but... I'm not gonna lie…
Never introduced myself.
Mhm. And only the NCPD tags people of interest, collects data…
I combed FIA data for info about you. Interesting profile.
You'd rather have the other guy?
Not a phrase I often hear in this trade.
Solomon Reed. Sleeper agent, seven years under a rock in NC. Undiagnosed paranoic.
Hah. Me to a T.
Solomon Reed – paranoid agent, but no one's told him yet.
Hm. Good or not – remains to be seen.
Don't mention it.
'S all good. Had to make sure. I'da done the same.
Wondering that myself.
Guess I'm… still tryna wrap my head around it.
Yeah, I feel ya. I get tasked with correcting someone else's mistakes, I do my own wrappin'.
V? How is she?
Try me.
A certain aircraft went down in Dogtown. We both know who was on board.
Apologies for the precautions.
Is that so?
Damn straight, I don't like it.
Security measures, precautions... Thought the token woulda done the job.
You'd be surprised. Not unusual in my line of biz.
Precautions, precautions…
It could be fake, simply counterfeit.
It's nothing personal. No hard feelings, I hope.
No, no hard feelings.
Indeed. You did not.
Scan me? NCPD databases wouldn't give you anything.
Never introduced myself.
I only ever risk so much. Sometimes it's just safer to shove the barrel of a Malorian between a choom's ribs, even if he is on your side.
Counterfeitin' a person is a lot harder.
Which means they may already have found Myers.
If so, good idea, poor execution.
You failed to cooperate… old habits kicked in.
